286
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:31,800
the company will be losing money.

287
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,170
We can tell the delivery riders

288
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,270
that this extra yuan

289
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:36,600
is a high-temperature allowance.

290
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,410
High-temperature allowance?

291
00:11:37,410 --> 00:11:39,490
What about a low-temperature allowance?

292
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,610
What about allowances for stormy weather?

293
00:11:41,610 --> 00:11:42,440
Mr. Wanghe,

294
00:11:42,610 --> 00:11:44,350
you'll only stay here for a year.

295
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:46,200
If you set such a high standard for us,

296
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:46,980
after you leave,

297
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:48,640
how are we supposed to move on?

298
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:49,560
Right?

299
00:11:49,590 --> 00:11:51,630
If you insist on going your own way

300
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:52,910
and raising the commission,

301
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:54,750
I hope you can get the head office

302
00:11:54,770 --> 00:11:55,710
to make rules about it.

303
00:11:55,710 --> 00:11:57,070
Each district will

304
00:11:57,100 --> 00:11:58,860
strictly follow the rules.

305
00:11:58,880 --> 00:11:59,500
That's no problem.

306
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:00,700
Am I right, everyone?

307
00:12:00,930 --> 00:12:02,500
Mr. Meng, what do you think?

308
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,220
Rules are rigid,

309
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:07,780
but people are flexible.

310
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,160
In fact,

311
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:11,170
in the company's commission standards,

312
00:12:11,170 --> 00:12:12,710
there are already provisions

313
00:12:12,710 --> 00:12:14,870
about temporarily raising the commission during extreme weather.

314
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:16,660
We're just specifying them.

315
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:20,640
Let's do this.

316
00:12:20,940 --> 00:12:21,610
Wanghe,

317
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:24,270
you'll be in charge of raising the commission.

318
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,090
But

319
00:12:25,740 --> 00:12:27,070
after it cools down,

320
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:28,720
you need to lower

321
00:12:28,740 --> 00:12:29,940
the commission back.

322
00:12:29,970 --> 00:12:31,170
No problem, Mr. Meng.

323
00:12:31,850 --> 00:12:32,980
Next,

324
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,510
our top priority

325
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:35,720
is to make preparations

326
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,050
to prevent heatstroke.

327
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:38,230
Each station

328
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:39,830
needs to prepare

329
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:42,190
heatstroke medicine and mung bean soup.

330
00:12:42,190 --> 00:12:43,150
In this regard,

331
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,360
Shao Xingchi's

332
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:46,770
Station 203 in Haidian District

333
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:47,960
has done a great job.

334
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:50,050
The delivery riders there are very satisfied.

335
00:12:50,050 --> 00:12:50,620
Additionally,

336
00:12:50,620 --> 00:12:52,820
the system needs to be optimized again.

337
00:12:52,970 --> 00:12:53,570
Haikuo.

338
00:12:54,050 --> 00:12:55,480
How long is the gap

339
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:57,680
between the time we give to delivery riders

340
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:59,410
and the time customers expect?

341
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:01,390
Usually three minutes.

342
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:03,350
The time shown to customers is 40 minutes,

343
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:04,720
while the time shown to delivery riders

344
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,200
is 37 minutes.

345
00:13:07,850 --> 00:13:08,490
Mr. Meng,

346
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:11,350
I suggest we shorten the time

347
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:13,840
given to delivery riders by another minute.

348
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:19,880
Everyone,

349
00:13:21,170 --> 00:13:23,410
great rewards will bring forth brave men.

350
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:26,340
If they can't do it, they don't have to take the order.

351
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,580
Wanghe,

352
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:32,870
simply shortening the system time

353
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:34,960
can only bring extensive growth.

354
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,420
Then what's your idea?

355
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:40,070
It's okay. Just speak your mind.

356
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,620
Mr. Meng.

357
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:45,810
The delivery riders of Bee

358
00:13:45,870 --> 00:13:47,270
currently use third-party mapping services.

359
00:13:47,270 --> 00:13:49,000
The odds of them providing the optimal routes

360
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,880
haven't reached 90% yet.

361
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:51,840
To some extent,

362
00:13:51,870 --> 00:13:53,270
this has affected the delivery efficiency.

363
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:54,120
So I suggest

364
00:13:54,150 --> 00:13:56,080
we launch our self-developed map ahead of schedule.

365
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:56,720
I've tested it.

366
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,880
It's already very stable.

367
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,010
It only needs final-stage debugging.

368
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:01,720
Isn't that too risky?

369
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:02,340
Haikuo,

370
00:14:03,190 --> 00:14:05,470
if you dare to take responsibility for your advice,

371
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:06,600
I'll dare to heed it.

372
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:07,670
Do you dare?

373
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,210
Of course.

374
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:11,090
If anything goes wrong with the self-developed map,

375
00:14:11,090 --> 00:14:13,090
I'll pack up and leave immediately.

376
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:14,720
Any other suggestions?

377
00:14:17,620 --> 00:14:18,700
If not,

378
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,380
we'll proceed with this plan.

379
00:14:20,530 --> 00:14:21,660
Meeting adjourned.

380
00:14:28,290 --> 00:14:29,290
Haikuo,

381
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:30,820
stay for a moment.

382
00:14:30,820 --> 00:14:32,080
I want to talk with you.

383
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,600
Sit down.

384
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:44,420
You're more excellent than I thought.

385
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:47,470
You flatter me, Mr. Meng.

386
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:49,780
Are you interested in coming to the headquarters?

387
00:14:49,780 --> 00:14:50,640
Headquarters?

388
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:53,190
To do what?

389
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:55,220
To be the Chief Technology Officer.

390
00:14:55,610 --> 00:14:57,320
The previous CTO

391
00:14:57,340 --> 00:14:59,060
was poached by Eat Well.

392
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:00,920
Well,

393
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:03,750
compared with having a headhunter poach someone,

394
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:04,530
I prefer

395
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:07,040
to promote someone in the company.

396
00:15:09,820 --> 00:15:10,610
Mr. Meng,

397
00:15:10,930 --> 00:15:13,110
Wanghe still needs help.

398
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:15,440
I need help too.

399
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:16,430
Haikuo,

400
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:18,900
you're a genius programmer.

401
00:15:19,010 --> 00:15:20,490
Running around for business with him

402
00:15:20,490 --> 00:15:21,890
is a waste of your talent.

403
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:24,990
How about this?

404
00:15:25,710 --> 00:15:26,900
Think it over.

405
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:29,240
Come to me when you've made up your mind.

406
00:15:30,740 --> 00:15:31,860
It's too sudden.

407
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,550
Please let me think about it.

408
00:15:34,590 --> 00:15:35,920
Whether you come or not,

409
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,320
you must keep it a secret.

410
00:15:37,420 --> 00:15:38,970
It involves backend data.

411
00:15:38,990 --> 00:15:39,870
Safety first.

412
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,820
[Bee Delivery]

413
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:51,870
What's going on?

414
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:52,380
[Bee Delivery]

415
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,980
Mr. Meng just asked me…

416
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:59,030
to keep up the good work.

417
00:15:59,050 --> 00:16:00,020
That's all.

418
00:16:00,380 --> 00:16:02,370
He didn't mention anything about a raise?

419
00:16:02,370 --> 00:16:02,980
No.

420
00:16:05,850 --> 00:16:06,450
It's okay.

421
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:07,470
Keep working.

422
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:09,540
Once our self-developed map is running smoothly,

423
00:16:09,540 --> 00:16:10,940
I'll apply for it for you.

424
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:13,460
Where's Xingchi?

425
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:14,190
Downstairs.

426
00:16:15,990 --> 00:16:17,630
[Fenghua Express]

427
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:35,260
[Fenghua Express]

428
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,230
Fenghua!

429
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:35,560
Fenghua!

430
00:16:35,940 --> 00:16:36,970
What's wrong?

431
00:16:37,890 --> 00:16:38,820
Are you okay?

432
00:16:39,780 --> 00:16:41,050
Sit down for a while.

433
00:16:41,210 --> 00:16:42,060
I'm fine.

434
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:43,930
I didn't have breakfast this morning.

435
00:16:43,930 --> 00:16:45,530
I think my blood sugar's low.

436
00:16:47,010 --> 00:16:47,960
Oh, you silly girl.

437
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:49,620
How could you skip breakfast?

438
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:55,580
Have some water.

439
00:16:57,580 --> 00:16:58,750
I'm fine.

440
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,770
Why are you so worried?

441
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,750
You're our backbone.

442
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:04,109
You can't go down.

443
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:05,550
I won't.

444
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:06,510
Don't worry.

445
00:17:12,109 --> 00:17:13,680
Finish the work you have on hand.

446
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:14,510
I must see it tomorrow.

447
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:16,440
Even if it means working overtime.

448
00:17:20,510 --> 00:17:21,240
Mr. Xie,

449
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,650
working late?

450
00:17:22,670 --> 00:17:23,599
I'll leave soon.

451
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,369
I'll head off then.

452
00:17:26,530 --> 00:17:28,329
How's the progress on your end?

453
00:17:30,810 --> 00:17:32,100
It's alright.

454
00:17:32,540 --> 00:17:34,230
What do you mean by alright?

455
00:17:35,060 --> 00:17:37,370
Where did you find those people?

456
00:17:37,850 --> 00:17:39,520
They're all so lazy.

457
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:42,210
They act like working overtime would kill them.

458
00:17:43,510 --> 00:17:45,640
Just pull your weight.

459
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:47,290
Why think so much?

460
00:17:47,590 --> 00:17:49,850
If the sky falls, the tall will hold it up.

461
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:50,910
Alright then.

462
00:17:50,910 --> 00:17:52,010
You hold on.

463
00:17:52,350 --> 00:17:53,160
I'm leaving.

464
00:17:53,180 --> 00:17:54,590
Aren't you having dinner with us?

465
00:17:54,590 --> 00:17:55,270
Another time.

466
00:17:55,270 --> 00:17:56,500
I have plans with Xiaohui.

467
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,590
Your girlfriend before friends, huh?

468
00:17:58,590 --> 00:18:00,250
Zhou Haikuo, you've changed.

469
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:02,040
You should date someone too.

470
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:03,920
I know you like being single,

471
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:06,390
but you can't stay single forever.

472
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:07,520
Get lost.

473
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:22,660
Do I look good?

474
00:18:24,940 --> 00:18:26,190
Yes.

475
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:27,570
Do you like it?

476
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:28,690
If you do, let's buy it.

477
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:30,480
It's over 3,000 yuan. Too expensive.

478
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:31,410
It's fine.

479
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:33,270
This month, I have overtime pay

480
00:18:33,270 --> 00:18:34,610
and a high-temperature allowance. I can afford it.

481
00:18:34,610 --> 00:18:36,010
And then live off scraps?

482
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,790
I can always earn more in the future.

483
00:18:37,790 --> 00:18:40,090
I'm competent anyway.

484
00:18:40,150 --> 00:18:42,170
You haven't established yourself at Bee yet.

485
00:18:42,170 --> 00:18:43,130
I have.

486
00:18:43,170 --> 00:18:45,100
Mr. Meng had a private talk with me.

487
00:18:45,620 --> 00:18:46,630
What did he say?

488
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:49,130
He wants me

489
00:18:49,390 --> 00:18:51,680
to work at headquarters as the CTO.

490
00:18:51,830 --> 00:18:53,260
Really?

491
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,340
What exactly did he say?

492
00:18:58,080 --> 00:18:59,310
I didn't agree.

493
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:01,510
Why?

494
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,880
Wanghe brought me into the company.

495
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:06,120
I need to discuss this with him first.

496
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:07,790
Wanghe doesn't know how to code.

497
00:19:07,790 --> 00:19:09,650
What's there to discuss with him?

498
00:19:10,260 --> 00:19:11,520
You don't understand.

499
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:15,480
No.

500
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:17,200
I don't understand.

501
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,060
I don't understand anything.

502
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:20,550
Then from now on,

503
00:19:20,550 --> 00:19:23,480
you don't need to tell me about these things anymore.

504
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:24,210
Wait.

505
00:19:25,090 --> 00:19:26,480
What did I say?

506
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:27,510
Wait.

507
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:28,860
Why are you upset?

508
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,260
You're on your period?

509
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:34,800
How about I get you some hot water?

510
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:38,800
What do you want to eat?

511
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:39,510
My treat.

512
00:19:39,540 --> 00:19:40,740
How about a barbecue?

513
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:44,500
I know

514
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,000
you and Wanghe are good friends,

515
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,500
and he's helped you a lot.

516
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,070
But you're an adult.

517
00:19:49,090 --> 00:19:51,530
You can only depend on yourself in the future.

518
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:52,750
I don't want my husband

519
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,270
to be someone who can't even decide

520
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:56,070
the direction of his own career!

521
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:00,320
Lion's head meatballs.

522
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:02,970
Braised shredded tofu.

523
00:20:06,260 --> 00:20:08,000
Stir-fried shredded eel.

524
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:10,430
Here's rice.

525
00:20:10,690 --> 00:20:11,890
Two servings of rice.

526
00:20:14,220 --> 00:20:16,570
Did you plant a bug on me?

527
00:20:17,810 --> 00:20:20,000
I mentioned this morning that I wanted to eat hometown food,

528
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,330
and you brought it to me.

529
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,290
Don't flatter yourself.

530
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:23,410
I want to eat it too.

531
00:20:23,550 --> 00:20:24,110
Here.

532
00:20:24,130 --> 00:20:24,760
Eat up.

533
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:31,890
How's it?

534
00:20:33,270 --> 00:20:34,180
Not quite there,

535
00:20:34,180 --> 00:20:35,110
but not bad.

536
00:20:36,550 --> 00:20:38,410
Haikuo's grandpa used to say that

537
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,560
when you crave hometown food,

538
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:41,810
you're not missing the food

539
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:42,810
but feeling homesick.

540
00:20:42,810 --> 00:20:43,530
What?

541
00:20:43,870 --> 00:20:44,900
You feel homesick?

542
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:46,030
Don't you miss home?

543
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:46,890
Occasionally,

544
00:20:47,140 --> 00:20:48,680
when I feel wronged.

545
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:50,440
I barely think about it other times.

546
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:51,300
What about you?

547
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,510
How did Xiang Yu die?

548
00:20:55,050 --> 00:20:57,050
Surrounded by enemies on all sides.

549
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:58,790
If a soldier keeps thinking about going home,

550
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:00,590
he'll lose the courage to fight.

551
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,010
I'm still fighting.

552
00:21:02,550 --> 00:21:04,000
You're a girl.

553
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:05,850
You can be vulnerable sometimes,

554
00:21:05,850 --> 00:21:06,880
but I can't.

555
00:21:07,110 --> 00:21:08,590
Everyone under me is watching.

556
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:09,640
I can't let them see

557
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,720
my vulnerable side,

558
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:11,720
not even once.

559
00:21:16,550 --> 00:21:18,350
I want to eat eel noodles.

560
00:21:18,350 --> 00:21:19,610
I'll make some for you.

561
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:20,960
Please don't.

562
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,680
Given your cooking skills,

563
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,270
I'd have a fishy taste in my mouth afterward.

564
00:21:24,270 --> 00:21:27,270
And I'd have to praise you against my better judgment.

565
00:21:28,350 --> 00:21:30,210
What's Xingchi been up to lately?

566
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:32,590
His cooking skills aren't good either.

567
00:21:32,590 --> 00:21:35,030
He learned to make eel noodles from Uncle Zhou.

568
00:21:35,030 --> 00:21:36,560
And lion's head meatballs.

569
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,110
Then go to him.

570
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:41,520
♫When the moon hangs in the sky♫

571
00:21:42,730 --> 00:21:43,890
♫And it's cooling in the yard♫

572
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:47,940
♫Who is still by your side?♫

573
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:48,920
Are you angry?

574
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:52,600
♫As time passes♫

575
00:21:49,790 --> 00:21:51,160
Seriously?

576
00:21:52,510 --> 00:21:53,880
Do you have to be so possessive?

